HEADWORD: Corybant
<hw>Cor"y*bant</hw> <pr>(k?r"?-b?nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> E. <plw>Corybants</plw> (-b<?/nts), oftener L.
<plw>Corybantes</plw> <pr>(-b<?/n"t<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>Corybas</ets>, Gr. <grk>Kory`bas</grk>.]</ety> <def>One of the
priests of Cybele in Phrygia. The rites of the Corybants were
accompanied by wild music, dancing, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

